### ============================================================
### TASK MODULE — API LIFECYCLE TESTS
### File: backend/api-tests/task.http
### ============================================================
### HOW TO USE:
### 1. Install REST Client extension in VS Code
### 2. Run: npm run dev
### 3. Run Block 0 first to get your seed IDs
### 4. Paste IDs into @variables below
### 5. Send each request top to bottom
### ============================================================


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 0 — GET SEED IDs
### ============================================================


### 0.1 — Get all users (copy manager ID)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 0.2 — Get all projects (copy a project ID)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 0.3 — Create a milestone to link tasks to
# @name seedMilestone
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/b53826f2-3f26-4b99-b168-8b83fe52c928/milestones
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Task Test Milestone",
  "due_date": "2026-08-31"
}

###

### ✏️ PASTE IDs here after running 0.1, 0.2, 0.3
@projectId   = PASTE_PROJECT_UUID_HERE
@managerId   = PASTE_MANAGER_UUID_HERE
@milestoneId = PASTE_MILESTONE_UUID_HERE


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 1 — CREATE
### ============================================================


### 1.1 — ✅ Create a full task with all fields (expect 201)
# @name task
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Prepare load-bearing analysis report",
  "description": "Document all load calculations for the north pylon.",
  "priority": "high",
  "due_date": "2026-07-15",
  "milestone_id": "{{milestoneId}}",
  "created_by": "{{managerId}}"
}

###

### ✏️ PASTE task ID here after running 1.1
@taskId = PASTE_TASK_UUID_HERE

### 1.2 — ✅ Create a minimal task (only required fields) (expect 201)
# @name minimalTask
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Quick inspection check",
  "created_by": "{{managerId}}"
}

###

### ✏️ PASTE minimal task ID here after running 1.2
@minimalTaskId = PASTE_MINIMAL_TASK_UUID_HERE

### 1.3 — ❌ NEGATIVE: title too short — under 2 chars (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "A",
  "created_by": "{{managerId}}"
}

###

### 1.4 — ❌ NEGATIVE: invalid priority value (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

