  "title": "Ghost Project Task",
  "created_by": "{{managerId}}"
}

###


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 2 — READ
### ============================================================


### 2.1 — ✅ Get task by ID (expect 200, includes milestone + assignees)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.2 — ✅ List all tasks for the project (expect 200, paginated)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.3 — ✅ Filter tasks by status=todo (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/tasks?status=todo
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.4 — ✅ Filter tasks by priority=high (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/tasks?priority=high
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.5 — ✅ Filter tasks by milestone_id (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/tasks?milestone_id={{milestoneId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.6 — ✅ Filter with pagination (expect 200, meta block present)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/{{projectId}}/tasks?page=1&limit=5
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.7 — ❌ NEGATIVE: task does not exist (expect 404)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.8 — ❌ NEGATIVE: project does not exist (expect 404)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

###


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 3 — UPDATE
### ============================================================


### 3.1 — ✅ Update title only (expect 200)
PUT http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Prepare load-bearing analysis report - Revised"
}

###

### 3.2 — ✅ Update priority only (expect 200)
PUT http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "priority": "critical"
}

###

### 3.3 — ✅ Update description only (expect 200)
PUT http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Updated: Include both north and south pylon calculations."
}

###

### 3.4 — ✅ Remove milestone linkage (set to null) (expect 200)
PUT http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "milestone_id": null
}

###

### 3.5 — ✅ Re-link to milestone (expect 200)
PUT http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "milestone_id": "{{milestoneId}}"
}

###

### 3.6 — ❌ NEGATIVE: empty body (expect 400)
PUT http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### 3.7 — ❌ NEGATIVE: title too short (expect 400)
PUT http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "X"
}

###

### 3.8 — ❌ NEGATIVE: invalid priority (expect 400)
PUT http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "priority": "extreme"
}

###

### 3.9 — ❌ NEGATIVE: task does not exist (expect 404)
PUT http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Ghost Task Update"
}

###


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 4 — STATUS MACHINE
### Valid path: todo → in_progress → blocked → in_progress → in_review → done
### ============================================================


### 4.1 — ✅ todo → in_progress (expect 200)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_progress"
}

###

### 4.2 — ✅ in_progress → blocked (expect 200)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "blocked"
}

###

### 4.3 — ✅ blocked → in_progress (expect 200)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_progress"
}

###

### 4.4 — ✅ in_progress → in_review (expect 200)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_review"
}

###

### 4.5 — ✅ in_review → done (expect 200, terminal state)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "done"
}

###

### 4.6 — ❌ NEGATIVE: done → todo (terminal — expect 400)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "todo"
}

###

### 4.7 — ❌ NEGATIVE: done → in_progress (terminal — expect 400)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_progress"
}

###

### 4.8 — ❌ NEGATIVE: done → blocked (terminal — expect 400)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "blocked"
}

###

### 4.9 — ❌ NEGATIVE: todo → done (skip — expect 400)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{minimalTaskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "done"
}

###

### 4.10 — ❌ NEGATIVE: todo → in_review (skip — expect 400)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{minimalTaskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_review"
}

###

### 4.11 — ❌ NEGATIVE: invalid status value (expect 400 from Zod)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{minimalTaskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "pending"
}

###

### 4.12 — ❌ NEGATIVE: missing status field entirely (expect 400)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{minimalTaskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### 4.13 — ❌ NEGATIVE: task does not exist (expect 404)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_progress"
}

###


